messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /invoices

All HTTP methods acceptable?
- false

Allowed methods (based on the code)
- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The main app mounts the invoices router at the prefix "/invoices" (index.js: app.use('/invoices', invoiceRoutes)). 
- In routes/invoices.js the route definitions are:
  - router.get('/', getInvoicesByUser) — registers GET on "/invoices"
  - router.post('/', createInvoice) — registers POST on "/invoices"
  - router.get('/count', ...) and router.get('/:id', ...), router.patch('/:id', ...), router.delete('/:id', ...) are for other paths under "/invoices" (e.g., "/invoices/count" or "/invoices/{id}"), not the root "/invoices".
- The controller getInvoicesByUser reads req.query.searchQuery, so the endpoint is GET /invoices with an optional query parameter searchQuery.
- I marked only methods explicitly registered in the code as acceptable. I did not assume framework behavior (such as automatic HEAD or OPTIONS handling by Express or the cors middleware), per your instruction.
